	<p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><i><b>The Mating Season</b></i> is a <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1951_in_film" title="1951 in film">1951</a> classic <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farce" title="Farce">farce</a> with elements of <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screwball_comedy" title="Screwball comedy">screwball comedy</a>. A film made by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paramount_Pictures" title="Paramount Pictures">Paramount Pictures</a>, it was directed by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mitchell_Leisen" title="Mitchell Leisen">Mitchell Leisen</a> and produced by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Brackett" title="Charles Brackett">Charles Brackett</a> from a <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screenplay" title="Screenplay">screenplay</a> by Charles Brackett, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Breen" title="Richard Breen">Richard Breen</a> and <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Walter_Reisch" title="Walter Reisch">Walter Reisch</a>, based on the play <i>Maggie</i> by Caesar Dunn. The <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ensemble_cast" title="Ensemble cast">ensemble cast</a> stars <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene_Tierney" title="Gene Tierney">Gene Tierney</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Lund" title="John Lund">John Lund</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miriam_Hopkins" title="Miriam Hopkins">Miriam Hopkins</a>, and <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thelma_Ritter" title="Thelma Ritter">Thelma Ritter</a>.</p>
